<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,829,1322]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,829,854]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1882" box="[285,411,829,854]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zoropsidae</taxonomicName>
were radically redelimited by Polotow 
<emphasis box="[883,943,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
(2015) and are consistently supported by molecular data, as well as by three homoplastic morphological synapomorphies on the male palp: presence of a type 2 ventral tibial process, a rounded to oval cymbium (
<figureCitation box="[816,908,901,926]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1972,1994]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,663,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,663,1949]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 9. Devendra spp. (A–C) D. pardalis (SImOn, 1898), FEmAlE; (A) hAbItus, dOrsAl VIEw; (B) AntErIOr VIEw OF OculAr ArEA;(C)EpIgynum, VEntrAl VIEw;(D–E) D. pumilus (SImOn, 1898), mAlE;(D)hAbItus,dOrsAl VIEw;(E)rIght pAlp,VEntrAl VIEw." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1076208/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Figs 9E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[921,971,902,926]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1906,1928]" captionTargetBox="[163,1412,935,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[151,1436,911,1884]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 11. Devendra pumilus (SImOn, 1898), mAlE. (A–C) lEFt pAlp; (A) VEntrAl VIEw; (B) rEtrOlAtErAl VIEw; (C) prOlAtErAl VIEw.AbbrEVIAtIOns: C, cOnductOr; E, EmbOlus; MA, mEdIAn ApOphysIs; RTA, rEtrOlAtErAl tIbIAl ApOphysIs; ST, subtEgulum; T, tEgulum; TI, tIbIA." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1076216/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">11A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[984,1034,902,926]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[168,1414,388,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,375,1871]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Devendra seriatus (SImOn, 1898). (A–C) lEFt mAlE pAlp; (A) VEntrAl VIEw; (B) rEtrOlAtErAl VIEw; (C) prOlAtErAl VIEw; (D–F) FEmAlE EpIgynum; (D) VEntrAl VIEw; (E) dOrsAl VIEw; (F) rIght spErmAthEcA,dOrsAl, clEArEd, dEtAIl.AbbrEVIAtIOns: C, cOnductOr; CD, cOpulAtOry ducts; E, EmbOlus; FD, FErtIlIZAtIOn duct; LL, lAtErAl lObE OF EpIgynum; LP, lAtErAl prOcEss OF EpIgynum; MA, mEdIAn ApOphysIs; ML, mEdIAn lObE OF EpIgynum; RTA, rEtrOlAtErAl tIbIAl ApOphysIs; S, spErmAthEcAE; T, tEgulum; TI, tIbIA." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1076218/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">12A</figureCitation>
) and a cymbial retrolateral process (absent from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[300,410,937,961]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Devendra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[300,410,937,961]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Devendra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,829,1322]" box="[199,1305,973,998]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,359,973,998]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Composition.</emphasis>
The family includes 26 genera and 178 species, distributed among four subfamilies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="64" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,829,1322]" box="[199,491,1009,1034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1009,1034]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Distribution.</emphasis>
Worldwide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,829,1322]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1045,1070]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Note on Griswoldiinae</emphasis>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[608,718,1045,1069]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Devendra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[608,718,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Devendra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[888,1061,1045,1070]" class="Arachnida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Machadoniinae">Machadoniinae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1076,1204,1045,1070]" class="Arachnida" family="Miturgidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Miturgidae</taxonomicName>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Lehtinen" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="LEhtInEn, P. T. (1967) ClAssIFIcAtIOn OF thE crIbEllAtE spIdErs And sOmE AllIEd FAmIlIEs, wIth nOtEs On thE EVOlutIOn OF thE subOrdEr ArAnEOmOrphA. Annales Zoologici Fennici, 4, 199 - 468." type="journal article" year="1967">Lehtinen (1967: 318)</bibRefCitation>
, later (
<bibRefCitation author="Griswold" box="[291,469,1081,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="GrIswOld, C. E. (1993) InVEstIgAtIOns IntO thE phylOgEny OF thE lycOsOId spIdErs And thEIr kIn (ArAchnIdA: ArAnEAE: LycOsOIdEA). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 539, 1 - 39. https: // dOI. Org / 10.5479 / sI. 00810282.539" type="journal article" year="1993">Griswold 1993</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Raven" box="[485,767,1081,1106]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="RAVEn, R. J. &amp; StumkAt, K. S. (2005) REVIsIOns OF AustrAlIAn grOund-huntIng spIdErs: II. ZOrOpsIdAE (LycOsOIdEA: ArAnEAE). Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 50, 347 - 423." type="journal article" year="2005">Raven &amp; Stumkat 2005</bibRefCitation>
) the genus was related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1896" box="[1089,1197,1081,1105]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Phanotea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1089,1197,1081,1105]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Phanotea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dippenaar-Schoeman &amp; Jocque" authorityYear="1997" box="[1262,1388,1081,1105]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Griswoldia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1262,1388,1081,1105]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Griswoldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(ex 
<emphasis box="[151,292,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Machadonia</emphasis>
). Silva Dávila (2003) recognized a clade named as “phanoteans” including 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dippenaar-Schoeman &amp; Jocque" authorityYear="1997" box="[1141,1267,1117,1141]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Griswoldia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1141,1267,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Griswoldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1896" box="[1281,1388,1117,1141]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Phanotea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1281,1388,1117,1141]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Phanotea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and an undescribed Chilean spider (later placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1882" box="[675,801,1153,1178]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zoropsidae</taxonomicName>
by Piacentini 
<emphasis box="[963,1012,1153,1177]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">et al</emphasis>
. 2013). The subfamily Griswoldiinae (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bertkau" authorityYear="1882" box="[158,288,1189,1214]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Zoropsidae</taxonomicName>
) was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Raven" box="[497,780,1189,1214]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="RAVEn, R. J. &amp; StumkAt, K. S. (2005) REVIsIOns OF AustrAlIAn grOund-huntIng spIdErs: II. ZOrOpsIdAE (LycOsOIdEA: ArAnEAE). Memoirs of the Queensland Museum, 50, 347 - 423." type="journal article" year="2005">Raven &amp; Stumkat (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, enlarged with the inclusion of the South American genera 
<taxonomicName authority="Mello-Leitao, 1915" authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1915" box="[151,462,1225,1250]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Itatiaya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,238,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Itatiaya</emphasis>
Mello-Leitão, 1915
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Polotow" box="[476,780,1225,1250]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="POlOtOw, D. &amp; BrEscOVIt, A. D. (2006) REVIsIOn OF thE NEOtrOpIcAl spIdEr gEnus Itatiaya MEllO-LEItaO (ArAnEAE, CtEnIdAE) wIth cOnsIdErAtIOns On bIOgEOgrAphIc dIstrIbutIOn OF spEcIEs. Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 23, 429 - 442. https: // dOI. Org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81752006000200018" type="journal article" year="2006">Polotow &amp; Brescovit 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Brescovit" box="[792,850,1226,1250]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="POlOtOw, D. &amp; BrEscOVIt, A. D. (2010) PhylOgEnEtIc rElAtIOnshIps OF thE NEOtrOpIcAl spIdEr gEnus Itatiaya (ArAnEAE). Zoologica Scripta, 40, 187 - 193. https: // dOI. Org / 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.2010.00463. x" type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Piacentini et al., 2013" authorityName="Piacentini et al." authorityYear="2013" box="[911,1288,1225,1250]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Cauquenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[911,1034,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Cauquenia</emphasis>
Piacentini 
<emphasis box="[1159,1215,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
, 2013
</taxonomicName>
, and recently redefined (Polotow 
<emphasis box="[398,468,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
2015) to include genera from Africa (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dippenaar-Schoeman &amp; Jocque" authorityYear="1997" box="[984,1110,1261,1285]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Griswoldia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[984,1110,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Griswoldia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1896" box="[1190,1297,1261,1285]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Phanotea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1190,1297,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Phanotea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Australia (
<taxonomicName authority="Raven, 2012" authorityName="Raven" authorityYear="2012" box="[160,476,1297,1322]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Austrotengella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[160,325,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Austrotengella</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Raven" box="[331,476,1298,1322]" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" refString="RAVEn, R. J. (2012) REVIsIOns OF AustrAlIAn grOund-huntIng spIdErs. V. A nEw lycOsOId gEnus FrOm EAstErn AustrAlIA (ArAnEAE: TEngEllIdAE). Zootaxa, 3305 (1), 28 - 52. https: // dOI. Org / 10.11646 / ZOOtAxA. 3305.1.2" type="journal article" year="2012">Raven, 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), South America (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mello-Leitao" authorityYear="1915" box="[681,768,1298,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Itatiaya" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[681,768,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Itatiaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[822,945,1298,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Cauquenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[822,945,1298,1321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Cauquenia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and Sri Lanka (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[1135,1245,1297,1321]" class="Arachnida" family="Zoropsidae" genus="Devendra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="13" pageNumber="64" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1135,1245,1297,1321]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="64">Devendra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
